Defendant Robert J Howard in court, in custody, with attorney Michael S. Holzman.   Debra Lynn Blasius appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed Sentence of:

6 Years Imprisonment (Credit - 36 days )
- 3 Years of Initial Confinement
- 3  Years of Extended Supervision

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Within 30 days be involved in a 12 step program and within 60 days have a sponsor/mentor;
- Perform  20 hours of community service each year of extended supervision with the last 20 hours to be completed with the first 10 months;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge;

DL REVOCATION:  36 months
IGNITITION INTERLOCK:  36 months

Defendant to attend the Victim Impact Panel  within the first 6 months of release onto extended sueprvison.

BLOOD DRAW FEE: $35.00  paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forwarded to Muskego Police Department.
TRANSCRIPT FEE:  $8.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forwarded to District Attorney's Office

FINE:2658.00  
DNA surcharge: $250.00
BAIL TO BE REFUNDED TO POSTER
(To be paid at the rate of $100.00  per month commencing on the 3rd month of release onto extended supervision and/or 296 hours of community service to be completed by the completion of extended supervision.  Court must receive notice of completion prior to due date)

Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program
